How the mattress and bedspread are chosen: women and men look for different things
Nothing from a pompous frame for the bed; what really lends its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, that is, the mattress and the bedspread.
First and foremost, they must be perfectly complemented so that they can be adapted to specific users.
During the choice numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, state of health and gender of the owner.
It is also important the type of interior in which the mattress and the bedspread are located.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cottage that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they "heat" more slowly.
In addition, they usually weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them around more frequently.
If the center channels are not properly aerated and above are on a firm base, they keep moisture inside.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence.
Those who have spent a lot of time abroad often use a very high mattress with a soft coat and will have trouble feeling good on a lower, harder surface.
“Almost all the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained that they didn’t sleep as well here.”
"For their crushed shoulders, heels and hips needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
"This type of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes who have problems with the nervous system, so they receive poor information from the joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in padded furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem anymore, because they have these suitable Tempur and Italian Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You no longer have to be an NHL player to appreciate viscoelasticity.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
Optimizes its stiffness and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not turn around like after a hard game.
He just sleeps better.
Viscoelastic also works as a protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to your height the length of your feet, i.e. between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example singles, it is recommended at least between 120 and 140 cm.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, you can apply a simple rule to calculate the width: when lying on your back, you should have your hands comfortably shrunk to your elbows," advises engineer Helena Prokopová, an expert at Cechu <0xC4><0x8D>alouník<0xC5><0xAF> a decoratér<0xC5><0xAF>, who has been dealing with the problem of healthy sleep and the ergonomics of furniture for many years.
In double rooms, each one needs its own bedspread and mattress, so during the purchase you have to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the bedspreads at different heights, which is not always possible on all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with springs interior a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softens.
"When you touch it with your hand or when you sit on the mattress, you should certainly not notice the springs," warns Helena Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a particular type of bedspread.
Fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
Mattresses breathe badly and you can not wash your cover, which today is often done.
And since every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a mattress life of up to 25 years or even a lifetime warranty.
However, everything has a but.
For this reason, sellers give a tip: on mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, take care of cleaning and washing the cover carefully, but better add a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Although mattress covers with zipper closure are currently manufactured throughout its perimeter, so when opening them they remain in two parts (something very important for the washing and the size of the washing machine!), their handling in the larger models (and by a single person) when lifting the mattress can seem a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a bedside table, do you have a firm board?
Never! Never!
As much for the beds designed for one night visits.
However, you should make (if you do not already have them) ventilation holes in the table and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-articulatable sheet bedspreads containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g., a combination of latex and coconut fiber) may be used, although a bedspread with a larger number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar region are reinforced and their rigidity can be regulated is always better.
Articulating sheet pads should not be used with a spring mattress, as it does not react to reclining.
In addition to adjusting the rigidity of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
It is a special fixation of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "surround" the shoulders perfectly during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, this is very important.
They are even remembered by the manufacturers of mattresses that, in the "males", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are so-called multi-torsion cushioned cross-frame or tablet beds.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the voltage is lowered.
You should also keep in mind that even if you use the right mattress and bedspread, if you use a bad pillow (large and "muffled"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow must hold the head and the corners can only reach to the shoulders, so that the muscles of them can be relaxed.
The recommended size is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying sideways, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with the shoulder-reinforced bed base or softer area of the mattress) as shoulder height.
Modern mattresses have something to do, it seems, with the original straw-filled mattresses.
Increasingly, manufacturers continue to use natural materials or, at least, mixtures.
In fact, organic mattresses are in fashion.
The petroleum-based raw materials, with which the polyurethane foam is manufactured, are filled with natural oils, for example castor or soybean.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers employ soybeans.
"Biologic, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin," explains Petr Va<0xC5><0xA1>í<0xC4><0x8D>ek of the company Tropico Plus.
Also, natural substances are used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh scent of forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men are "cooled" with breeze vegetable extracts, so that the mattress cover absorbs heat and cools the body, women prefer to "heat" the cover.
Red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so women feel more warmth.
Favourites now?
Cold foam mattresses, which are more porous, have an adapted cell structure, which makes them more permeable than normal polyurethane mattresses and offer more permeability.
The combination of various cold and viscoelastic foam stiffnesses makes it possible to manufacture mattresses of various zones that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who perform a therapeutic function usually have a lower VAT, since they are considered as sanitary means.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It is difficult to save on mattresses and bedspreads.
Sometimes you can approve offers from manufacturers or sellers, who sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a memory foam attached to the case for 11,990 crowns.
The second one is free.
The era of viscoelasticism with an open cellular structure and high density began with Tempur's "cosmic" material.
Initially it emerged as material for NASA, because during the take-offs astronauts were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempur softens in the heat and hardens in the cold.
Therefore, the warm human body exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores from occurring, but also to improve comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foam is not only used in mattresses, but also for medical devices, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
Domestic manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and the like.
More and more parents are using people-tracking devices to monitor their children
Fear for children leads more and more people to think about monitoring them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also track the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, in case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old girl Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka Janatková.
At the moment the device has the approximate size of a matchbox, but it will soon shrink to the size of a watch.
Many people were frightened by the case of the missing Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka and began to report on the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
"We're all trying to tell ourselves that it's not spying, it's another way to decrease the chances of a tragedy," says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
“I recognize that, in certain cases, you can abuse such devices, for example if they get into someone’s bag without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases.”
“Most customers actually buy it for security reasons,” Pilin adds.
In his opinion, children should always know what the "box" is for and how it is used in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bo<0xC4><0x8D>ková warns about the fact that if the child does not want to carry it, he will simply throw it away.
“Even the youngest children show great creativity when it comes to intentionally losing certain things if they want to avoid being controlled.”
“In the past, parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but they could be turned off as easily as the tracking device,” Bo<0xC4><0x8D>ková says.
In his opinion, it is questionable whether in the event of an attack such a device is really useful.
“If it is a prepared kidnapping, the perpetrator will practically always check if the child is carrying any kind of electronic device that can reveal his or her location.”
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices expands, it will also look for them, since their sale will undoubtedly be made with a lot of publicity."
“In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police,” says the psychologist.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an impromptu attack by a pedophile.
According to Robert <0xC4><0x8C>ech of the company RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is destroyed immediately, its presence can help.
"The device can be configured to send the position regularly after a certain period."
“If he suffers damage, he will at least facilitate the last position of the person in question.”
“The most expensive devices have a built-in tilt meter, so if the person simply slips and remains immobile, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question,” says <0xC4><0x8C>ech.
In his view, such a service can be obtained even with smartphones with navigation, in which only special software must be installed.
The problem with current tracking units is that at the moment they are devices with a similar size to a matchbox or smaller mobile phones.
Therefore, they can be lost.
According to Pilin of Macro Weil, that is why tests are currently being conducted with devices that look like a digital clock.
"In addition, they will have the added advantage that a potential attacker may not identify the device."
“Or identifying him after a certain time, which can save the police time,” he adds.
Even if the tracking devices are worn on the wrist or hanging, they will still use the same technology that is used for vehicle tracking.
This is the position check with a GPS system (which is used in the usual navigation in the car) combined with the function of a mobile phone that communicates the current position.
The army has enough wicks to encircle the whole of the Czech Republic, but they only last two years.
The Czech army bought 445 kilometers of wick to set up explosives.
Already last year the Ministry of Defense added 224 kilometers of wick to its arsenal.
Therefore, they have stocks for 225 years.
The problem is that the lifespan of the wick is two years, four at most.
The army bought the explosives wick from STV Group, a. s. for forty million kroner.
The General's staff responded to MF DNES justifying the purchase of such an enormous amount of wick by saying that the soldiers need for the training maneuvers 60 kilometers of wick a year.
According to the calculations of the army pyrotechnicians, with whom MF DNES was in contact, it is decided, however, that, in such a case, they should perform such manoeuvres with frequent use of explosives every year also all generals, high command officers, and even secretaries and cleaners.
Neither Defense Minister Alexandr Vondr nor Army Captain Vlastimil Picek wanted to be exempt.
Only in this way could it be justified for the army to spend sixty kilometers of wick.
Such a length is equivalent to 25,000 explosions.
Even if it were, the army would have enough stocks for more than ten years.
If on the contrary, as experts say, for the initial training of each new professional arrives with a maximum of two meters of wick, the army would have with the new purchase (even adding the consumption of the units of engineers or special) sufficient stocks for the 225 indicated above.
The soldiers of the rapid-intervention brigade complained personally recently to Minister Vondra because they say they barely have ammunition for various weapons, thus limiting even the practice of shooting for money.
And let’s not talk about the lack of underwear.
"I also cannot understand that they repeatedly buy us such quantities of wick."
“But it’s their decision and they’ll certainly know why they act like that.”
“For us, the military is a good customer that we as a company try to satisfy,” admits STV Group sales director Jan D<0xC4><0x9B>ck<0xC3><0xBD>.
Defense Ministry spokesman Jan Pej<0xC5><0xA1>ek defends the hundreds of miles of wick, saying he will also have stockpiles of this "ammunition" for at least ten years.
However, Jan D<0xC4><0x9B>ck<0xC3><0xBD> of STV Group indicates that the wick only has a shelf life of four years and, in the case of pyrotechnic products for the army or the police, two years.
"If stored in perfect conditions, it can last up to four," says one of the soldiers who, due to possible criticism from the army, does not want to give his name.
After the end of its useful life, each ammunition should be carefully checked to see if it is still reliable and will not harm the soldiers.
But these tests are not free and require additional investment.
Another argument of the Ministry is that, by buying 445 kilometers of wick, he got a discount.
“They cost us 60% less than last year’s order of 244 kilometers,” said Pej<0xC5><0xA1>ek, a spokesman for the Defense Ministry’s shopping center.
Just to compare: the annual wick consumption of the police pyrotechnicians, who remove the ammunition from the Second World War or that left by the Soviet army, no longer exceeds 1,500 meters.
In addition, the police always ask only the right amount to deplete the ammunition before its useful life ends.
They decided this for safety reasons for pyrotechnicians and, in the meantime, more modern and reliable wick types can be obtained.
The Ministry already has clear difficulties in finishing tens of thousands of tons of ammunition from the time of the Warsaw Pact, when the Czechoslovak army of two hundred thousand people was preparing for a campaign on the Rhine.
According to the pyrotechnicians with whom MF DNES spoke, after a couple of years the following problem will occur with the current one: it will be necessary to eliminate hundreds of kilometers of old wick, which is now being bought "cheap".
