"The L-159 single-seaters, on the other hand, were separated from the long-repaired aircraft, with no additional investments or contributions from the Ministry."
"The two-seater L-159T1s were exchanged in their current state," he told Právo Pej<0xC5><0xA1>ek.
He added that the army does not run out of two-seater aircraft, since in May 2009 the army signed a contract with Aer Vodochody for the amount of 200 million crowns for the construction of four unnecessary L-159 devices for two-seater aircraft.
