It is in fact a powerful process simulation software that the German company put on the market in 2007 for purposes far removed from the high competition.
Called PLM, this powerful computing instrument has been used to design assembly lines of manufacturing factories around the world, power plants, high precision instruments.
The objective is to reproduce, faithfully simulate the product or process before building it in a real way, thus avoiding failures and avoidable expenses.
PLM has facilitated the development of Canon’s cameras, Sukhoi planes and Nissan’s most famous utility cars.
Siegfried Russwurm, head of Siemens’ industrial division, explains that the use of this computer tool in its Formula 1 factory has allowed Red Bull to design and implement in “a few hours, almost in real time” the modifications, changes and improvements that are detected during races and in trials.
